WEBVTT

00:02.713 --> 00:07.468
♪ How do I say goodbye ♪

00:07.468 --> 00:14.555
♪ To what we had? ♪

00:14.555 --> 00:20.141
♪ The good times
 that made us laugh ♪

00:20.141 --> 00:21.942
♪ Outweigh the bad ♪

00:21.942 --> 00:23.904
So, this is why you took
a sick day from work --

00:23.904 --> 00:25.816
to make a slide show?

00:25.816 --> 00:29.950
Do you know how hard it is
to choose just the right song?

00:29.950 --> 00:32.493
You know, I tried it at first
with "I'll Make Love to You."

00:32.493 --> 00:34.155
It felt okay over Obama

00:34.155 --> 00:36.787
but got a little weird
over Sasha and Malia.

00:36.787 --> 00:37.918
Yeah.

00:37.918 --> 00:39.960
That's where it got weird.

00:39.960 --> 00:41.372
Okay.

00:41.372 --> 00:42.793
All right, then.

00:45.546 --> 00:47.798
♪♪

00:47.798 --> 00:49.670
Dre: She doesn't get it.

00:49.670 --> 00:52.843
With Obama leaving office,
 it's made me think.

00:52.843 --> 00:55.676
Obama was more than just
 the first black president.

00:55.676 --> 00:58.058
He was the culmination
 of years of struggle

00:58.058 --> 01:00.101
to make sure our votes counted.

01:00.101 --> 01:03.774
1869 -- Congress passes
 the 15th Amendment,

01:03.774 --> 01:05.736
giving black men
 the right to vote.

01:05.736 --> 01:09.900
1896 -- Louisiana passes
 the Grandfather Clause

01:09.900 --> 01:12.993
to keep former slaves and
 their descendants from voting.

01:12.993 --> 01:17.158
Registered black voters
 drop from 44% to 4%.

01:17.158 --> 01:20.501
Through the 1940s,
 poll taxes, literacy tests,

01:20.501 --> 01:23.294
and violent threats
 prevent blacks from voting.

01:23.294 --> 01:27.758
1964 -- the 24th Amendment
 makes poll tax illegal,

01:27.758 --> 01:31.382
and over 250,000 new
 black voters are registered.

01:31.382 --> 01:34.135
2008 -- Obama.

01:34.135 --> 01:38.599
2011 -- three states pass
 restrictive photo I.D. laws

01:38.599 --> 01:41.142
to try to stop us
 from voting again.

01:41.142 --> 01:43.023
Where we are is so tenuous

01:43.023 --> 01:45.065
and can be so easily
 taken away.

01:45.065 --> 01:47.898
That's why this current
 election is so important.

01:47.898 --> 01:49.530
No, not this one.

01:49.530 --> 01:50.941
This one.

01:50.941 --> 01:52.943
Junior is running for
 student body president

01:52.943 --> 01:54.325
against this guy.

01:54.325 --> 01:55.996
It may seem a little crazy

01:55.996 --> 01:59.200
that I'm investing real time
 into a high-school election,

01:59.200 --> 02:01.452
but the world's losing
 one black president.

02:01.452 --> 02:03.664
And I want to make sure
 to give it another.

02:03.664 --> 02:06.917
The future of our entire race
 rests on Junior.

02:06.917 --> 02:09.880
Okay, which one's
more believable?

02:09.880 --> 02:12.463
This one? This one?

02:12.463 --> 02:15.756
One more time.
This one? This one?

02:15.756 --> 02:17.558
This one? This one?

02:17.558 --> 02:20.851
Yep, this is my guy,
 and getting him elected

02:20.851 --> 02:23.063
was going to be harder
 than tricking America

02:23.063 --> 02:27.067
into putting a black man
 in the White House -- twice.

02:27.067 --> 02:29.690
Why aren't you answering?

02:29.690 --> 02:32.573
♪♪

02:32.573 --> 02:34.945
Why do we keep getting
this magazine Black Braids?

02:34.945 --> 02:36.777
I don't know.
Why are you asking me?

02:36.777 --> 02:37.828
Uh...

02:37.828 --> 02:40.491
Okay, it's mine.

02:40.491 --> 02:42.743
Too damn old to be ashamed
of my proclivities.

02:42.743 --> 02:43.994
Yeah. Okay.

02:43.994 --> 02:45.496
Keep an eye out
for Tax Evader.

02:45.496 --> 02:47.127
It won't have my name on it,
for obvious reasons.

02:47.127 --> 02:49.210
Ooh, ballots came today.

02:49.210 --> 02:51.001
Huh.

02:51.001 --> 02:52.713
What?

02:52.713 --> 02:54.555
-They changed our polling place.
-Of course they did.

02:54.555 --> 02:56.056
They want to make it harder
for us to find them.

02:56.056 --> 02:57.798
That there's the reason
I don't vote in the first place.

02:57.798 --> 02:59.510
[ Chuckling ]
You're kidding, right?

02:59.510 --> 03:01.892
You vote.
You have to vote.

03:01.892 --> 03:03.264
[ Clicks tongue ]
Of course you vote.

03:06.807 --> 03:08.108
You don't vote, do you?

03:08.108 --> 03:10.190
Why should I?
The election's rigged.

03:10.190 --> 03:12.403
He's right. Why else you think
Bernie isn't the candidate?

03:12.403 --> 03:13.984
Because
Hillary got more votes.

03:13.984 --> 03:15.446
-Or did she?
-She did.

03:15.446 --> 03:17.077
Maybe that's just what
they want you to believe.

03:17.077 --> 03:18.779
-Because it's the truth.
-Whose truth?

03:18.779 --> 03:20.951
-I'm not doing this with you.
-And I'm not voting this year.

03:20.951 --> 03:24.084
What's wrong with you?
We weren't raised that way.

03:24.084 --> 03:26.206
[ Chuckles ] We were raised
to boycott non-hemp fibers

03:26.206 --> 03:27.748
and use leeches
as Band-Aids,

03:27.748 --> 03:29.089
so that argument's
not great.

03:29.089 --> 03:31.001
Sideshow Bob here's got a point,
Rainbow.

03:31.001 --> 03:32.333
The system is broken.

03:32.333 --> 03:34.214
No, you're broken.

03:34.214 --> 03:35.716
And you are setting
a bad example for my son.

03:35.716 --> 03:37.638
No, they're right.

03:37.638 --> 03:38.839
They're rigging the vote
at school.

03:38.839 --> 03:40.100
What are you talking about?

03:40.100 --> 03:42.843
We're "supposedly" voting
for a new class pet.

03:42.843 --> 03:45.476
They say it's between a parrot,
a snake, and a guinea pig.

03:45.476 --> 03:46.847
But who are they kidding?

03:46.847 --> 03:49.310
They're not gonna let us get
something cool like a snake.

03:49.310 --> 03:51.231
Damn right, 'cause that's
a free-thinking animal.

03:51.231 --> 03:53.734
And it's not like they want
our vote anyway.

03:53.734 --> 03:56.947
They're having it during lunch
on chicken stars day.

03:56.947 --> 03:58.449
Yeah, no one's gonna
show up for that.

03:58.449 --> 03:59.530
Classic voter suppression.

03:59.530 --> 04:01.201
Okay.

04:01.201 --> 04:02.823
You need to
suppress your face.

04:02.823 --> 04:04.365
So aggressive.

04:04.365 --> 04:05.956
Ooh, is that the new
  Black Braids?

04:05.956 --> 04:10.040
♪♪

04:10.040 --> 04:11.632
All right, guys,
I'm gonna need

04:11.632 --> 04:13.584
all hands on deck
for this campaign.

04:13.584 --> 04:15.376
Zoey, public liaison.

04:15.376 --> 04:16.677
Nope.

04:16.677 --> 04:18.839
Copy that.
Jack, you are on snack duty.

04:18.839 --> 04:19.839
Huh?

04:19.839 --> 04:21.882
Uh...never mind.

04:21.882 --> 04:24.184
Diane, accounts manager.

04:25.556 --> 04:28.018
I will do everything
in my power

04:28.018 --> 04:30.521
to make sure
your candidate loses.

04:30.521 --> 04:32.313
You know,
I appreciate your candor,

04:32.313 --> 04:34.445
but I'm gonna
need that button back.

04:34.445 --> 04:36.947
Oh, let me see this,
Junior.

04:36.947 --> 04:40.361
"A new day with Andre."
Okay.

04:40.361 --> 04:43.744
"Friend to some,
acquaintance to many,

04:43.744 --> 04:45.996
unknown to most."

04:45.996 --> 04:47.708
Huh.
-Don't worry.

04:47.708 --> 04:51.081
I've been preparing for this day
since I started high school.

04:51.081 --> 04:54.004
If elected, I would be the most
qualified president ever.

04:54.004 --> 04:56.377
-Mm-hmm?
-Perfect attendance,

04:56.377 --> 04:59.259
stellar grades,
every committee allowable,

04:59.259 --> 05:01.882
and I hit every
janitor retirement party.

05:01.882 --> 05:03.053
Why?

05:03.053 --> 05:04.925
You sound like my opponent.

05:04.925 --> 05:09.730
There are three keys to the
perfect election-day outfit --

05:09.730 --> 05:13.604
breathability, walkability,
sensuability.

05:13.604 --> 05:15.275
We didn't fight
for civil liberties

05:15.275 --> 05:17.147
so Grandma could vote
in sweat pants.

05:17.147 --> 05:18.489
Who are you voting for?

05:18.489 --> 05:20.941
Whoever the Democrat is,
baby.

05:20.941 --> 05:23.744
Without knowing where they stand
on any issue?

05:23.744 --> 05:24.865
Seems ignorant.

05:24.865 --> 05:26.286
Would it seem ignorant

05:26.286 --> 05:28.288
if I slapped the taste
out of your mouth?

05:28.288 --> 05:31.582
Oh, sweetie.
Oh, sweetie, I'm so sorry.

05:31.582 --> 05:33.834
Sometimes Grandma forgets
she's been saved.

05:33.834 --> 05:36.667
[ Chuckles ]
Listen, precious. Listen.

05:36.667 --> 05:40.551
Ignorance is being unaware of
the dangers of the kitten heel.

05:40.551 --> 05:43.173
♪♪

05:43.173 --> 05:45.806
[ Heel snaps ]
Oh! Oh! Oh!

05:45.806 --> 05:46.887
No!
[ Ding ]

05:46.887 --> 05:50.100
No! Not Buchanan!

05:50.100 --> 05:51.972
90% of Buchanan votes

05:51.972 --> 05:54.395
were because the elderly
picked the wrong shoe.

05:54.395 --> 05:56.977
[ Chuckles ]
-Your priorities seem off.

05:56.977 --> 06:01.031
God, Idris, alimony.

06:01.031 --> 06:02.983
My priorities are just fine,
darling.

06:02.983 --> 06:04.485
[ Chuckles ]

06:04.485 --> 06:08.328
Lord, why is this child
testing me today?

06:08.328 --> 06:11.702
Zoey, guess who I saw
at the store.

06:11.702 --> 06:12.703
No.

06:12.703 --> 06:14.254
Cara's mom.

06:14.254 --> 06:17.167
She said Cara got early
admission into Princeton.

06:17.167 --> 06:19.590
That's incredible.
-Well, not really.

06:19.590 --> 06:21.922
Cara looks like somebody
who needs to be smart.

06:21.922 --> 06:23.343
Okay, you know what?
Say what you want to say.

06:23.343 --> 06:25.305
She's going to Princeton.

06:25.305 --> 06:28.098
Hey, how is
your application coming?

06:28.098 --> 06:30.771
You want to bounce any
essay ideas off your mom?

06:30.771 --> 06:32.142
I mean, I know I'm a doctor,

06:32.142 --> 06:33.894
but I'm also
kind of a wordsmith.

06:33.894 --> 06:36.066
You know,
God gaveth with both hands.

06:36.066 --> 06:37.317
I'll be fine, Mom.

06:37.317 --> 06:38.729
I have a 3.6.

06:38.729 --> 06:40.230
3.6?

06:40.230 --> 06:42.362
Pssht.
Those are army grades.

06:42.362 --> 06:46.026
Excuse me. I had a 3.6,
and I went to Brown.

06:46.026 --> 06:48.829
Yeah,
back when Coke was a dime.

06:48.829 --> 06:50.581
Good luck, soldier.

06:50.581 --> 06:51.992
♪♪

06:51.992 --> 06:54.585
♪ Outweigh the bad ♪

06:54.585 --> 06:56.627
[ Man sobbing ]

06:56.627 --> 06:59.960
Everyone needs to see this.

06:59.960 --> 07:01.922
We can get him a third term.

07:01.922 --> 07:03.634
-That's what I'm talking about.
-Mm-hmm.

07:03.634 --> 07:07.347
I will pay my own money
to take this around the country.

07:07.347 --> 07:08.679
Or we could just
put it on YouTube.

07:08.679 --> 07:10.551
I kind of wanted
to see America.

07:10.551 --> 07:13.764
Okay. M-Maybe we can take it
to the YouTube office.

07:13.764 --> 07:15.606
Is it in America?

07:15.606 --> 07:16.897
Yeah.

07:16.897 --> 07:18.689
Okay, cool.
I'm cool with that.

07:18.689 --> 07:20.320
Hey,
what are you guys watching?

07:20.320 --> 07:22.152
[ Laptop closes ]
-Dre's Obama memorial.

07:22.152 --> 07:23.654
[ Gasps ] Did he die?

07:23.654 --> 07:24.905
-No.
-Oh.

07:24.905 --> 07:26.366
He's just leaving office.

07:26.366 --> 07:27.988
So he can go and die?

07:27.988 --> 07:30.200
His term is over.

07:30.200 --> 07:31.992
Oh. You mean,
his -- his life term?

07:31.992 --> 07:34.575
What is your deal
with Barack?

07:34.575 --> 07:38.038
My deal is that there are
thousands of children out there

07:38.038 --> 07:40.250
who have never had
a white president.

07:40.250 --> 07:42.082
How are they gonna know that
they have opportunities?

07:42.082 --> 07:43.884
This is crazy.

07:43.884 --> 07:47.007
Barack Obama is the best
president we've ever had.

07:47.007 --> 07:48.178
-[ Laughs ]
-Uh, yeah,

07:48.178 --> 07:49.970
if Reaganomics
never took root

07:49.970 --> 07:52.262
and saved the western world
from living in caves.

07:52.262 --> 07:54.054
Fact.

07:54.054 --> 07:56.807
Boom.
You both know my son Connor.

07:56.807 --> 07:58.689
Never seen him before
in my life.

07:58.689 --> 08:01.692
Oh, I'm sorry. You probably know
him as the New Haven Ripper.

08:01.692 --> 08:03.273
Excuse me?

08:03.273 --> 08:07.197
It's just a silly name that
the "victims" gave my baby boy

08:07.197 --> 08:08.869
for crimes they couldn't prove

08:08.869 --> 08:10.320
that he was aware
that he had committed.

08:10.320 --> 08:13.784
Anywho [chuckles]
Obama's a bad guy.

08:13.784 --> 08:15.495
Yeah, you want to
talk about strangling,

08:15.495 --> 08:16.747
just look at what he's done
to our economy.

08:16.747 --> 08:19.459
Who's talking
about strangling?

08:19.459 --> 08:21.792
We're not -- per the settlement
with the families.

08:21.792 --> 08:24.084
This is exactly what
I'm talking about.
 Mm-hmm.

08:24.084 --> 08:25.926
As soon as Barack leaves office,

08:25.926 --> 08:27.628
they're gonna forget
all the good he's done.
 Mm-hmm.

08:27.628 --> 08:30.340
Well, I'm not gonna forget
that Barack Hussein Obama

08:30.340 --> 08:31.682
is a foreign-born Muslim,

08:31.682 --> 08:34.845
and he also let Bin Laden sleep
in the Lincoln Bedroom.

08:34.845 --> 08:37.397
Okay, Connie, now,
that's just home talk,

08:37.397 --> 08:39.730
but, yes, fact.
-Yeah, right?

08:39.730 --> 08:42.192
Talking to Stevens
 and the New Haven Ripper

08:42.192 --> 08:44.695
made it clear that
 there are a lot of Americans

08:44.695 --> 08:46.907
who can't wait
 to get rid of Obama,

08:46.907 --> 08:49.029
which meant it was
 more important than ever

08:49.029 --> 08:50.821
for Junior to win
 this election.

08:50.821 --> 08:52.452
Hey, son,
how'd your speech go today?

08:52.452 --> 08:54.284
If you can get past
all the projectiles

08:54.284 --> 08:55.866
and the booing,
it went great.

08:55.866 --> 08:58.328
Okay, looks like your speech
needed a little help.

08:58.328 --> 08:59.660
Let's roll up our sleeves.

08:59.660 --> 09:01.421
Let's do this.

09:01.421 --> 09:05.295
Yah-ah-ah, are you wearing
a flared pantsuit?

09:05.295 --> 09:07.467
Yep. Hugs my frame.

09:07.467 --> 09:10.430
Um, sweetheart, I-I think
that's a woman's suit.

09:10.430 --> 09:12.302
What? No.

09:12.302 --> 09:14.675
The lady at the thrift store
said it was European.

09:14.675 --> 09:15.886
They have women in Europe.

09:15.886 --> 09:17.137
Yeah.

09:17.137 --> 09:18.769
There were clues --

09:18.769 --> 09:21.481
the hard candy in the pockets...
-Yeah.

09:21.481 --> 09:22.943
...the shoulder pads.

09:22.943 --> 09:24.685
The fact that
it's a woman's pantsuit.

09:24.685 --> 09:27.688
I can't recover from this.
I'm doomed...

09:27.688 --> 09:30.781
because of one bad speech
in an unflattering pantsuit.

09:30.781 --> 09:32.863
Oh, my God.
You're being Hillary-ed.

09:32.863 --> 09:35.495
Hillary-ed.
That's it.

09:35.495 --> 09:38.038
We are done.
-Wha--

09:38.038 --> 09:39.700
And to think,
I would've been

09:39.700 --> 09:41.581
the school's first
black president.

09:41.581 --> 09:43.503
What?

09:43.503 --> 09:45.045
What did you just say?

09:45.045 --> 09:48.128
Your school has never had
a black president?

09:48.128 --> 09:50.010
No.

09:50.010 --> 09:53.764
And just like that, I knew
 how Junior was going to win.

09:53.764 --> 09:55.215
What's Ortho Tri-Cyclen?

09:55.215 --> 09:56.807
It's birth control,
sweetheart.

09:56.807 --> 09:58.518
So many clues.

10:03.563 --> 10:04.935
Junior being one of the only
 black kids at school

10:04.935 --> 10:06.186
was finally gonna pay off
 in this election.

10:06.186 --> 10:09.820
Pea coat, New Balance,
and Frisbee.

10:09.820 --> 10:11.652
They all go in the trash.

10:11.652 --> 10:13.613
-But that's who I am.
-Not anymore it's not.

10:13.613 --> 10:15.696
We are in
the last days of disco

10:15.696 --> 10:18.118
of it being cool to be black,
son.

10:18.118 --> 10:19.790
They are coming
for our coolness.

10:19.790 --> 10:21.952
Pitbull is out there,

10:21.952 --> 10:23.834
Bieber is right around
the corner,

10:23.834 --> 10:26.046
but for now,
it's still ours.

10:26.046 --> 10:28.208
And we're gonna use it
to get you elected.

10:28.208 --> 10:30.711
Okay.
I think I understand.

10:30.711 --> 10:33.253
-Do you?
-You know I don't.

10:33.253 --> 10:34.965
I'm just saying this
because I want you to leave

10:34.965 --> 10:36.807
so I can get my Frisbee
out of the trash.

10:36.807 --> 10:40.851
♪♪

10:40.851 --> 10:43.183
What about a ferret?

10:43.183 --> 10:44.474
You need to
stay out of this.

10:44.474 --> 10:46.646
A ferret? What is this,
a damn joke to you?

10:46.646 --> 10:48.068
We're talking about
a class pet here.

10:48.068 --> 10:49.229
The boy needs
something realistic,

10:49.229 --> 10:51.111
like a shark or a bald eagle.

10:51.111 --> 10:53.193
-There it is.
-Mm-hmm.

10:53.193 --> 10:54.574
You know what?

10:54.574 --> 10:55.776
Doesn't even matter.

10:55.776 --> 10:57.948
I got a detention
for talking in class,

10:57.948 --> 10:59.199
and now
they won't let me vote.

10:59.199 --> 11:01.411
Classic felony
disenfranchisement.

11:01.411 --> 11:03.203
Are we still talking about
a class pet?

11:03.203 --> 11:04.624
No, we're talking about
the rules.

11:04.624 --> 11:06.246
You get in trouble one time
in this country,

11:06.246 --> 11:08.208
you don't get to vote in it
for the rest of your life.

11:08.208 --> 11:09.589
Unless you're in Maine
or Vermont.

11:09.589 --> 11:11.251
You could be in jail
and vote there.

11:11.251 --> 11:12.923
Oh, yeah, the whitest states
in America

11:12.923 --> 11:14.634
let their white felons vote.

11:14.634 --> 11:15.796
So messed up.

11:15.796 --> 11:17.507
W-What would you
even call that?

11:17.507 --> 11:19.800
That is white justice.

11:19.800 --> 11:21.101
You got that right.

11:21.101 --> 11:22.682
Preach.

11:22.682 --> 11:23.804
♪♪

11:23.804 --> 11:24.895
Hey, girl.

11:24.895 --> 11:26.807
-I'm busy.
-Awesome.

11:26.807 --> 11:31.111
So [clicks tongue] I was just
thinking about your application,

11:31.111 --> 11:33.153
and -- yeah, okay --

11:33.153 --> 11:36.236
about the fact that a big part
of your college essay

11:36.236 --> 11:38.408
is gonna be the activities
that you do outside of school.

11:38.408 --> 11:40.080
So what are you
thinking of listing?

11:40.080 --> 11:41.742
Nothing.

11:41.742 --> 11:43.874
Sweetie, come on.
[ Giggles ]

11:43.874 --> 11:46.957
There must be something.
I mean, um, drama?

11:46.957 --> 11:49.419
Newspaper.
Oh, debate team.

11:49.419 --> 11:51.752
Quit. Nope. Ew.

11:51.752 --> 11:56.096
Okay, so when -- w-when
I ask you what's going on

11:56.096 --> 11:57.597
and you say "nothing,"

11:57.597 --> 12:00.340
do you actually
mean nothing?

12:00.340 --> 12:01.802
Relax.

12:01.802 --> 12:03.343
Everything
I've been reading says

12:03.343 --> 12:05.345
the essay is
the most important part...

12:05.345 --> 12:07.017
-Uh-huh?
-...and I'm gonna nail it.

12:07.017 --> 12:09.940
Okay. Okay.
